WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.052 --> 00:00:10.662
Previously onFrom...

2
00:00:10.793 --> 00:00:12.363
You can't keep
punishing yourself. Boyd.

3
00:00:12.490 --> 00:00:13.620
She wouldn't have wanted that.

4
00:00:13.752 --> 00:00:16.322
And I wish you had
the luxury of grief.

5
00:00:16.451 --> 00:00:19.061
but you don't.
These people need you.

6
00:00:19.193 --> 00:00:21.373
I knew all about the divorce
and how this whole trip

7
00:00:21.499 --> 00:00:23.019
was just one last hurrah

8
00:00:23.153 --> 00:00:24.763
before you sat us down
to break the news.

9
00:00:24.894 --> 00:00:27.904
Thomas is dead!
You have two other kids!

10
00:00:28.028 --> 00:00:29.728
Why aren't we enough for you?

11
00:00:33.772 --> 00:00:36.652
Hello?
Is anybody out there?

12
00:00:42.694 --> 00:00:45.054
Seriously. man. I don't know why
you keep staring at that thing.

13
00:00:45.175 --> 00:00:47.525
Yeah. there's two pages
stuck together here.

14
00:00:49.527 --> 00:00:50.437
Whoa. whoa. whoa.

15
00:00:55.533 --> 00:00:57.493
Holy shit.

16
00:00:57.622 --> 00:00:59.282
I have Sara tied up
in the basement of the church.

17
00:00:59.407 --> 00:01:01.277
She showed me this.

18
00:01:01.409 --> 00:01:03.449
Something was
watching me that day.

19
00:01:03.585 --> 00:01:05.065
the same thing that told Sara--

20
00:01:05.195 --> 00:01:07.495
And you think this thing
is trying to help us?

21
00:01:07.632 --> 00:01:09.462
Whatever it is. it's a part
of the fabric of this place.

22
00:01:09.591 --> 00:01:11.811
They're in the house!
They're inside!

23
00:01:17.425 --> 00:01:19.295
Follow protocol!

24
00:01:19.427 --> 00:01:21.387
Find your buddy.
get into the van!

25
00:01:21.516 --> 00:01:22.556
Ellis! We have to
get back in the house!

26
00:01:22.691 --> 00:01:25.091
We have to get inside!
I have an idea. Come on!

27
00:01:28.653 --> 00:01:30.223
Please. please. please. please!

28
00:01:30.351 --> 00:01:31.311
We have to go.

29
00:01:31.439 --> 00:01:33.439
Go where?
Where are we going?

30
00:01:33.571 --> 00:01:35.231
You go first.

31
00:01:35.356 --> 00:01:36.966
I'll follow you down.

32
00:01:37.097 --> 00:01:39.317
We need to get to town.

33
00:01:39.447 --> 00:01:40.667
No. We have to go to the trees.

34
00:01:40.796 --> 00:01:41.966
You're crazy.

35
00:01:42.102 --> 00:01:44.282
You have to get inside.

36
00:01:44.408 --> 00:01:45.708
-The tree? No! No!
-You'll be safe!

37
00:01:45.844 --> 00:01:47.324
-What?
-I promise.

38
00:01:47.455 --> 00:01:48.975
Find your brother.
You have to tell him.

39
00:01:49.109 --> 00:01:50.939
I'll be right behind you!

40
00:01:55.637 --> 00:01:57.897
No!
No. come here!

41
00:02:00.598 --> 00:02:02.248
Stay with me.

42
00:02:24.448 --> 00:02:25.448
Hey. Sheriff?

43
00:02:25.580 --> 00:02:27.150
Yep.

44
00:02:28.365 --> 00:02:30.235
In a sec.

45
00:02:37.418 --> 00:02:38.938
I got. uh--

46
00:02:39.071 --> 00:02:40.681
I got most of the Colony House
residents squared away.

47
00:02:40.812 --> 00:02:43.122
Most people in town aren't
really using their basements.

48
00:02:43.250 --> 00:02:45.560
so each house is
gonna take two or three.

49
00:02:45.687 --> 00:02:47.167
Some are at the clinic and. uh.

50
00:02:47.297 --> 00:02:49.517
the last three are gonna
stay with me and my mom...

51
00:02:49.647 --> 00:02:52.427
and Jade. I guess.

52
00:02:52.563 --> 00:02:54.653
Okay.

53
00:02:54.783 --> 00:02:57.663
Feels like things are starting
to get tense out there.

54
00:02:57.786 --> 00:03:00.216
People are already
boarding up their windows.

55
00:03:00.354 --> 00:03:02.574
and with Colony House and
the town living together now.

56
00:03:02.704 --> 00:03:05.494
I think maybe we should get
everyone gathered together

57
00:03:05.620 --> 00:03:07.710
and. I don't know.
say something?

58
00:03:07.839 --> 00:03:09.539
It's a good idea.

59
00:03:09.667 --> 00:03:12.667
You should do that.

60
00:03:13.323 --> 00:03:16.333
I think it would mean
a lot more coming from you.

61
00:03:17.588 --> 00:03:18.888
Right.

62
00:03:19.634 --> 00:03:21.294
Right.

63
00:03:22.506 --> 00:03:24.676
Are you okay?

64
00:03:26.510 --> 00:03:28.640
He saved my life.
You know that?

65
00:03:28.773 --> 00:03:31.693
Father Khatri.
the night we got into town.

66
00:03:31.820 --> 00:03:34.210
he risked his own life
to make sure that...

67
00:03:36.738 --> 00:03:38.868
-Give everyone my regards.
-Wait. Where are you going?

68
00:03:39.001 --> 00:03:40.091
I got something to do.
It's important.

69
00:03:40.220 --> 00:03:42.050
More important than this?

70
00:03:42.700 --> 00:03:45.400
Sheriff. the people
need you right now.

71
00:03:45.529 --> 00:03:47.099
-They need to hear that--
-What?

72
00:03:47.227 --> 00:03:49.267
They need to hear what?

73
00:03:49.403 --> 00:03:51.233
Everything's gonna be okay?
That God's got a plan.

74
00:03:51.361 --> 00:03:53.581
Look. if you're gonna be
the sheriff when I'm gone.

75
00:03:53.711 --> 00:03:55.711
you're gonna need to start
figuring out how to say things

76
00:03:55.844 --> 00:03:58.804
like that for yourself
and sound halfway convincing.

77
00:03:58.934 --> 00:04:01.724
You'll do fine.

78
00:04:05.810 --> 00:04:16.040
♪

79
00:04:23.915 --> 00:04:26.265
Let's take a walk.

80
00:04:36.493 --> 00:04:41.543
♪

81
00:06:42.402 --> 00:06:43.792
♪ And if I had a boat

82
00:06:43.925 --> 00:06:46.095
-Come on!
-♪ I'd go out on the ocean

83
00:06:46.231 --> 00:06:48.361
-Listen to those lyrics.
-♪ And if I had a pony

84
00:06:48.495 --> 00:06:50.665
Listen to how
peaceful that sounds.

85
00:06:50.801 --> 00:06:54.631
The man is riding
a pony on an ocean.

86
00:06:54.762 --> 00:06:58.462
You know why?
'Cause he has a boat.

87
00:06:58.592 --> 00:07:00.862
Doesn't matter how many times
you listen to the song.

88
00:07:00.985 --> 00:07:02.805
still can't afford
to buy a boat.

89
00:07:02.944 --> 00:07:05.384
Yeah. look. all I'm saying is
if we manage the payments--

90
00:07:05.512 --> 00:07:07.212
Oh. we're gonna
manage the payments?

91
00:07:07.339 --> 00:07:09.819
-Yeah!
-Right.

92
00:07:09.951 --> 00:07:11.741
So. is not paying the payments
one of the management options?

93
00:07:11.866 --> 00:07:14.776
Because that's
the option we'd be taking.

94
00:07:14.912 --> 00:07:16.742
Yeah. I'm pretty sure most
lenders frown on that option.

95
00:07:16.871 --> 00:07:18.871
Yeah. yeah. Listen.
nobody's talking to you.

96
00:07:19.003 --> 00:07:21.793
-All right? Nobody.

97
00:07:21.919 --> 00:07:23.829
You know what they used
to call e in the army. right?

98
00:07:23.965 --> 00:07:25.355
Mr. Fish and Loaves.

99
00:07:25.488 --> 00:07:27.188
That's right!
That's right! That's right!

100
00:07:27.316 --> 00:07:28.796
They'd send me to
any base to set it up.

101
00:07:28.926 --> 00:07:31.446
and no matter what they gave me.
no matter what the resources.

102
00:07:31.581 --> 00:07:33.281
I would make it work.
Yes. sir. that's right.

103
00:07:33.409 --> 00:07:34.579
Mr. Fish and Loaves.

104
00:07:34.715 --> 00:07:35.925
...Loaves.

105
00:07:36.064 --> 00:07:38.374
Yeah. but. you know. didn't
they call mom Iron Abby?

106
00:07:38.501 --> 00:07:40.331
They certainly did.
And don't you forget it.

107
00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:43.110
Yeah. yeah.
I hear you.

108
00:07:43.245 --> 00:07:45.985
The problem with iron is...
rigid.

109
00:07:46.117 --> 00:07:49.507
So. sometimes. you know.
it doesn't know when to bend.

110
00:07:49.643 --> 00:07:50.563
Uh-huh.

111
00:07:50.687 --> 00:07:53.857
Babe... Babe...
all I'm saying.

112
00:07:53.995 --> 00:07:55.945
all I'm saying is. a boat.

113
00:07:56.084 --> 00:07:59.354
you know. wouldn't be
a bad retirement gift.

114
00:07:59.479 --> 00:08:01.479
In case you
needed some ideas

115
00:08:01.611 --> 00:08:05.051
on how to help me. you know.
smooth my transition

116
00:08:05.180 --> 00:08:09.450
from a long and decorated
military career to. you know.

117
00:08:09.576 --> 00:08:11.876
this strange and mysterious
civilian life.

118
00:08:12.013 --> 00:08:14.803
And a boat-- Babe. what are--
what are you looking for?

119
00:08:14.929 --> 00:08:16.889
My-my Chapstick. I can't
find anything in this bag.

120
00:08:17.018 --> 00:08:19.368
Can you hold this for me?

121
00:08:19.499 --> 00:08:21.809
Sure.
What is-- Is--

122
00:08:21.936 --> 00:08:24.806
This--
This looks like a boat key.

123
00:08:24.939 --> 00:08:26.769
-What?
-What?

124
00:08:26.897 --> 00:08:29.507
Yeah. why am I holding
a-a boat key?

125
00:08:29.639 --> 00:08:31.689
-Wait. did you buy the boat?

126
00:08:31.815 --> 00:08:33.465
-Oh. shit.

127
00:08:33.600 --> 00:08:35.820
Of course we
bought you a boat!

128
00:08:35.950 --> 00:08:37.870
-Oh. snap!
-If I had to listen to that man

129
00:08:37.995 --> 00:08:39.865
sing about Tonto and
his pony one more time.

130
00:08:39.997 --> 00:08:41.737
I'd throw myself into traffic.

131
00:08:41.869 --> 00:08:43.389
-Oh. snap!
-Happy retirement. Dad!

132
00:08:43.523 --> 00:08:45.313
You bought me a boat. baby!

133
00:08:45.437 --> 00:08:46.607
-Thank you!
-Dad!

134
00:08:46.743 --> 00:08:48.623
Oh!

135
00:08:57.798 --> 00:08:58.888
Oh. God.

136
00:09:05.022 --> 00:09:07.502
Please.

137
00:09:07.634 --> 00:09:09.904
can you just tell me
where we're going?

138
00:09:10.027 --> 00:09:11.677
Where's Father Khatri?

139
00:09:13.901 --> 00:09:16.601
They used to shriek.
Did you know that?

140
00:09:16.730 --> 00:09:21.040
All night long. they'd shriek.
Drove people crazy.

141
00:09:21.691 --> 00:09:24.431
That all stopped
once we got the talismans.

142
00:09:24.564 --> 00:09:25.744
Then they started to whisper.

143
00:09:25.869 --> 00:09:28.049
I always wondered about that.

144
00:09:28.176 --> 00:09:30.566
Your voices tell you
anything about that?

145
00:09:31.832 --> 00:09:33.362
No.

146
00:09:33.485 --> 00:09:36.265
'Course not. God forbid
they tell you anything useful.

147
00:09:37.272 --> 00:09:39.492
Keep walking.

148
00:09:39.622 --> 00:09:42.282
Not until you
tell me what's going on.

149
00:09:42.407 --> 00:09:43.837
You think you're
gonna stand there

150
00:09:43.974 --> 00:09:45.454
and make demands
after what you did?

151
00:09:45.585 --> 00:09:46.715
Where is Father Khatri?

152
00:09:46.847 --> 00:09:48.757
He's dead!

153
00:09:48.892 --> 00:09:50.292
What?

154
00:09:50.415 --> 00:09:51.895
Those things got
into Colony House.

155
00:09:52.026 --> 00:09:55.456
Father Khatri tried to help.
Now he's dead.

156
00:09:55.595 --> 00:09:57.945
along with a lot
of other people.

157
00:09:58.075 --> 00:10:00.075
Is Ellis okay?

158
00:10:02.906 --> 00:10:05.866
He's fine.
He's scraped up.

159
00:10:05.996 --> 00:10:08.776
He's back at the clinic
with the others.

160
00:10:10.131 --> 00:10:11.871
Oh. now you wanna cry.

161
00:10:12.002 --> 00:10:14.792
You cry like that
for Bing Qian?

162
00:10:14.918 --> 00:10:17.008
You think I'm a monster.

163
00:10:17.138 --> 00:10:19.138
I don't give
two shits what you are.

164
00:10:19.270 --> 00:10:21.840
The only reason you're alive
is because Father Khatri

165
00:10:21.969 --> 00:10:23.489
thought you could
help us all get home.

166
00:10:23.623 --> 00:10:25.063
The second you prove him wrong.

167
00:10:25.189 --> 00:10:28.019
I'm gonna put
a bullet in you myself.

168
00:10:28.149 --> 00:10:30.109
Now. keep walking.

169
00:10:32.022 --> 00:10:33.722
-Where are we going?
-I said keep walking!

170
00:10:44.252 --> 00:10:46.212
So. I'll make up some beds
for you in the basement.

171
00:10:46.341 --> 00:10:48.951
Uh. bathroom's in the back and
feel free to use the kitchen.

172
00:10:49.083 --> 00:10:51.003
but you've gotta
respect the rations.

173
00:10:51.128 --> 00:10:52.958
It won't be the most
comfortable thing in the world.

174
00:10:53.087 --> 00:10:54.517
but we should have Colony House
back up

175
00:10:54.654 --> 00:10:56.004
and running pretty soon. so...

176
00:10:56.133 --> 00:10:58.223
What the fuck is this?

177
00:10:58.353 --> 00:11:00.923
Uh. we're gonna have a few more
house guests for a little while.

178
00:11:01.051 --> 00:11:05.101
And how little
is a little while?

179
00:11:05.229 --> 00:11:07.539
Aren't you the guy that thought
this was a giant escape room?

180
00:11:07.667 --> 00:11:09.447
How'd that work out for you?

181
00:11:09.581 --> 00:11:10.841
-Fuck off.
-Okay.

182
00:11:10.974 --> 00:11:12.674
All right.
this is bullshit. okay?

183
00:11:12.802 --> 00:11:14.372
They chose the flower.
They don't belong here.

184
00:11:14.499 --> 00:11:15.629
Dude. why don't
you just--

185
00:11:15.762 --> 00:11:16.852
All right.
any of you guys know Victor?

186
00:11:16.980 --> 00:11:19.940
All right. where's he squatting?
I need to find him.

187
00:11:20.070 --> 00:11:21.900
I saw him running
towards the woods

188
00:11:22.029 --> 00:11:23.599
with the Matthews
girl last night.

189
00:11:23.726 --> 00:11:25.946
Fantastic.
See what a little intercommunity

190
00:11:26.076 --> 00:11:28.726
cooperation can do?
Kumbay-fucking-ya!

191
00:11:30.341 --> 00:11:31.911
Let's get inside.

192
00:11:32.039 --> 00:11:34.129
That guy's
the fuckin' worst.

193
00:11:34.258 --> 00:11:37.258
I don't--
I don't even understand.

194
00:11:37.392 --> 00:11:39.922
It was like one second everyone
was having such a good time--

195
00:11:40.047 --> 00:11:41.957
How-- How did you
get out of the house?

196
00:11:42.876 --> 00:11:45.526
I was-- I was up in
Victor's room and we--

197
00:11:45.661 --> 00:11:47.751
No. It...

198
00:11:47.881 --> 00:11:49.931
-It wasn't like that. We were...
-Julie...

199
00:11:50.057 --> 00:11:52.017
No. he was stacking
all of these.

200
00:11:52.146 --> 00:11:53.966
and it looked like he was
getting ready to leave.

201
00:11:54.104 --> 00:11:56.114
And then.
when the screaming started.

202
00:11:56.237 --> 00:11:58.667
we climbed out his window.

203
00:11:58.805 --> 00:12:00.545
and he said we had
to go to the forest.

204
00:12:00.676 --> 00:12:03.236
And then. we ran to this tree
and then he pushed me inside--

205
00:12:03.374 --> 00:12:05.074
-Hey.
-And I...

206
00:12:05.202 --> 00:12:06.902
He said it was starting.

207
00:12:07.030 --> 00:12:08.510
What was starting?

208
00:12:08.640 --> 00:12:10.730
I don't know. He...

209
00:12:13.820 --> 00:12:16.080
All I know is. one second.
I was in a tree.

210
00:12:16.213 --> 00:12:18.963
and the next. I was in a
giant cabinet in a root cellar.

211
00:12:19.086 --> 00:12:20.126
How is that possible?

212
00:12:20.261 --> 00:12:22.871
You went through a Farway Tree!

213
00:12:23.003 --> 00:12:25.013
Huh?

214
00:12:25.135 --> 00:12:28.225
Victor said you can
go all sorts of places.

215
00:12:28.356 --> 00:12:32.006
And sometimes people
go to different places.

216
00:12:32.142 --> 00:12:34.102
So. maybe he went
somewhere else.

217
00:12:34.231 --> 00:12:36.061
We have to find him!

218
00:12:36.190 --> 00:12:38.930
One step at a time.
Hey. Julie...

219
00:12:41.238 --> 00:12:42.888
Jules...
Hey. Jules.

220
00:12:45.025 --> 00:12:46.455
Julie...

221
00:12:48.115 --> 00:12:50.985
What's happening to us?
What--?

222
00:12:51.118 --> 00:12:52.948
-Honey...
-What is going on?

223
00:12:53.076 --> 00:12:54.026
What's happening?

224
00:12:54.164 --> 00:12:56.124
We're digging a big hole
in the basement.

225
00:12:56.253 --> 00:12:58.603
We're gonna find out where
the electricity comes from.

226
00:12:58.734 --> 00:13:00.874
Hey. hey. No.

227
00:13:02.172 --> 00:13:03.872
Jules. we're gonna be fine.
Breathe.

228
00:13:05.132 --> 00:13:06.662
I know.
Everything's gonna be okay.

229
00:13:06.786 --> 00:13:08.396
-Yes.
-No! How can you say that?

230
00:13:08.526 --> 00:13:10.656
What part of this is okay?

231
00:13:10.790 --> 00:13:13.050
Honey. oh my God.
Just...

232
00:13:13.183 --> 00:13:16.063
Ah. Good. you're here.
Have you seen Victor?

233
00:13:16.186 --> 00:13:17.796
-Hey!
-One of the squatters

234
00:13:17.927 --> 00:13:19.927
at my house said you ran off to
the woods with him last night!

235
00:13:20.060 --> 00:13:20.970
Ow! Ow!

236
00:13:21.104 --> 00:13:22.154
Hey!
I need to talk to her!

237
00:13:22.279 --> 00:13:25.109
What is wrong with you?!

238
00:13:25.239 --> 00:13:27.149
Do you have any idea
what she has been through?

239
00:13:27.284 --> 00:13:29.114
Look. believe me. I get it.
Times are tough all around.

240
00:13:29.243 --> 00:13:31.513
But I found
something last night!

241
00:13:32.986 --> 00:13:35.986
There is this symbol that
I've been-- I've been seeing.

242
00:13:36.119 --> 00:13:37.689
The same symbol is in this book.

243
00:13:37.817 --> 00:13:39.167
And last night. okay.
last night.

244
00:13:39.296 --> 00:13:40.816
I found this photo!

245
00:13:40.950 --> 00:13:42.260
I don't give a shit
about your questions

246
00:13:42.386 --> 00:13:44.256
and your symbol and your books.

247
00:13:44.388 --> 00:13:46.648
Just stay the fuck away
from my daughter.

248
00:13:46.782 --> 00:13:48.922
You understand me?

249
00:13:51.004 --> 00:13:55.184
Okay. you're doing the whole
protective dad thing.

250
00:13:55.312 --> 00:13:57.052
I respect that.

251
00:13:57.184 --> 00:14:00.144
You dragged me out
into the woods.

252
00:14:00.274 --> 00:14:03.154
have me climb a fuckin' tree
for some stupid idea.

253
00:14:03.277 --> 00:14:05.147
and then you
run off like a psycho

254
00:14:05.279 --> 00:14:07.059
before we even have
a chance to try it.

255
00:14:07.194 --> 00:14:10.594
Yeah. uh.
I'm sorry about that...

256
00:14:10.719 --> 00:14:12.029
It worked.

257
00:14:14.331 --> 00:14:16.251
-Wait. What?
-Yeah.

258
00:14:16.377 --> 00:14:19.987
All I got was some static.
but it worked.

259
00:14:23.253 --> 00:14:25.043
I think if we get it
up over the tree line.

260
00:14:25.168 --> 00:14:26.298
and we get it enough power.

261
00:14:26.430 --> 00:14:28.080
I think we could
get a signal out.

262
00:14:28.215 --> 00:14:29.345
Wait. wait. wait.

263
00:14:29.477 --> 00:14:31.867
How do you propose we
get up over the tree line?

264
00:14:33.263 --> 00:14:35.923
We start by going
to the high ground.

265
00:14:39.095 --> 00:14:48.235
♪

266
00:14:48.365 --> 00:14:50.585
Jesus. That's grim.

267
00:14:56.460 --> 00:14:59.070
Where are
all the people?

268
00:14:59.202 --> 00:15:00.682
I mean...

269
00:15:01.552 --> 00:15:03.212
Wait!

270
00:15:03.337 --> 00:15:05.247
-Whoa. Boyd!
-Jesus!

271
00:15:05.382 --> 00:15:08.042
Hey!
Hey. hey. back up!

272
00:15:09.169 --> 00:15:10.339
Back up!

273
00:15:10.474 --> 00:15:12.874
You tryin' to get
yourself killed?

274
00:15:12.999 --> 00:15:14.519
I need you to
listen to me. please.

275
00:15:14.652 --> 00:15:16.652
Okay?
There isn't much time.

276
00:15:16.785 --> 00:15:20.345
Now. this is gonna
sound very. very strange.

277
00:15:20.484 --> 00:15:22.144
and you're not
gonna believe me.

278
00:15:22.269 --> 00:15:24.179
and I wouldn't
believe me either. Okay?

279
00:15:24.314 --> 00:15:25.934
And I wish there was
more time to explain.

280
00:15:26.055 --> 00:15:27.535
But if you don't come
with me right now.

281
00:15:27.665 --> 00:15:30.145
you're all going to die.

282
00:15:30.277 --> 00:15:32.627
-Oh...
-Okay. whoa. whoa. whoa. Mom.

283
00:15:32.757 --> 00:15:34.667
Mom. what the hell
are you doing?

284
00:15:34.803 --> 00:15:36.763
Okay. you have a gun.
That is good.

285
00:15:36.892 --> 00:15:39.942
And you're welcome to keep it
pointed at me the entire time.

286
00:15:40.069 --> 00:15:43.859
But I am begging you.
please come with me.

287
00:15:43.986 --> 00:15:46.816
Go on.
Drive away. Drive away.

288
00:15:46.946 --> 00:15:48.426
No. no. no. no. Please.

289
00:15:51.385 --> 00:15:54.295
What the hell was that?

290
00:15:54.431 --> 00:15:56.351
That was death.

291
00:15:56.477 --> 00:15:58.957
and it's coming...
right now.

292
00:16:00.394 --> 00:16:03.274
Please.

293
00:16:13.450 --> 00:16:15.670
Let's go.

294
00:16:26.942 --> 00:16:30.032
You can put that thing away now.

295
00:16:30.163 --> 00:16:32.033
The only things that are
gonna hurt you are out there.

296
00:16:32.165 --> 00:16:34.295
and that thing's not gonna
make a damn bit of difference

297
00:16:34.428 --> 00:16:35.688
if they find us.

298
00:16:35.820 --> 00:16:41.650
Look. I know you
all have questions.

299
00:16:42.479 --> 00:16:46.479
And. I promise. we will talk
when the sun comes up.

300
00:17:03.500 --> 00:17:04.720
-Okay.
-Ah...

301
00:17:04.849 --> 00:17:05.889
-Here we go. all right?
-Okay.

302
00:17:06.025 --> 00:17:07.235
-Nice and slow.
-Okay.

303
00:17:07.374 --> 00:17:08.424
It's gonna hurt a bit.
Just breathe.

304
00:17:08.549 --> 00:17:10.639
-Yeah.
-Good. good. good.

305
00:17:10.768 --> 00:17:11.378
-There we go.

306
00:17:11.508 --> 00:17:12.728
-Breathe.

307
00:17:12.857 --> 00:17:14.337
Good.
Breathe. breathe. breathe.

308
00:17:14.468 --> 00:17:16.168
Relax. Down. Good.

309
00:17:16.296 --> 00:17:17.336
Okay. see?
Good as new.

310
00:17:17.471 --> 00:17:18.601
Yeah.

311
00:17:18.733 --> 00:17:20.303
-All right.
-Yeah.

312
00:17:20.430 --> 00:17:21.910
Just gonna put a sling on here.

313
00:17:22.041 --> 00:17:23.171
Can I help with anything?

314
00:17:23.303 --> 00:17:25.873
Make sure
he doesn't get out of bed. Okay?

315
00:17:26.001 --> 00:17:27.311
I don't want you going anywhere

316
00:17:27.437 --> 00:17:30.007
until I can give you
a solid once-over.

317
00:17:30.136 --> 00:17:31.346
-Yeah.
-All right?

318
00:17:32.790 --> 00:17:34.230
Here we go. You good?

319
00:17:36.011 --> 00:17:37.231
Be back in
a second. okay?

320
00:17:37.360 --> 00:17:39.230
Thank you.

321
00:17:39.362 --> 00:17:41.632
Hey.

322
00:17:41.756 --> 00:17:43.446
Busy day for you.

323
00:17:43.584 --> 00:17:45.244
Uh. yeah. we're
a little short-handed.

324
00:17:45.368 --> 00:17:46.848
What can I do?

325
00:17:46.978 --> 00:17:48.278
Well. I could use some help

326
00:17:48.415 --> 00:17:49.845
getting this place
a bit more secure.

327
00:17:49.981 --> 00:17:51.941
It's gonna be a full house
tonight. given what happened.

328
00:17:52.071 --> 00:17:53.641
-So...
-Yeah. of course.

329
00:17:53.768 --> 00:17:55.988
Oh. I. um...

330
00:17:56.118 --> 00:17:59.378
I. uh...
I finished Chapter 6. It's...

331
00:17:59.513 --> 00:18:01.343
Things are starting
to get interesting.

332
00:18:01.471 --> 00:18:02.341
Yeah. I don't think
it's gonna be

333
00:18:02.472 --> 00:18:04.302
much of a reading
night tonight. but. uh.

334
00:18:04.431 --> 00:18:05.911
yeah. I'll try to check it out.

335
00:18:06.041 --> 00:18:07.221
Cool.

336
00:18:10.741 --> 00:18:12.571
Thanks. Deputy.

337
00:18:26.322 --> 00:18:27.582
Donna.

338
00:18:37.594 --> 00:18:40.424
You got a minute?

339
00:18:40.554 --> 00:18:42.694
How's Julie?

340
00:18:42.817 --> 00:18:45.247
She's okay.

341
00:18:45.385 --> 00:18:46.815
She's. uh...

342
00:18:46.951 --> 00:18:49.351
But that--
that's not why I'm here.

343
00:18:49.476 --> 00:18:51.426
We came because
we need your help.

344
00:18:51.565 --> 00:18:52.475
With what?

345
00:18:54.481 --> 00:18:56.611
We wanna build a tower

346
00:18:56.744 --> 00:18:58.274
and we wanna
put it on the roof.

347
00:18:58.398 --> 00:18:59.358
What?

348
00:18:59.486 --> 00:19:00.786
We think if we can
get it high enough.

349
00:19:00.922 --> 00:19:04.102
we could
broadcast a signal

350
00:19:04.230 --> 00:19:06.360
that anyone else
in the area could hear.

351
00:19:06.493 --> 00:19:09.023
And what area
is that exactly?

352
00:19:09.148 --> 00:19:12.538
Look. whatever
this place is.

353
00:19:12.673 --> 00:19:16.463
wherever this place is.

354
00:19:16.590 --> 00:19:19.510
radio signals work
in ways that we can't.

355
00:19:19.636 --> 00:19:22.336
And we already got a strong
indication that this could work.

356
00:19:24.293 --> 00:19:26.513
Well...
We got a little static.

357
00:19:26.643 --> 00:19:29.473
C--Colony House

358
00:19:29.603 --> 00:19:32.483
is the highest point
on the highest hill.

359
00:19:32.606 --> 00:19:34.696
And if we build a tower
and we put it up there.

360
00:19:34.825 --> 00:19:37.125
we could broadcast out a signal
that could get up over

361
00:19:37.263 --> 00:19:40.883
any interference
from the forest canopy.

362
00:19:43.399 --> 00:19:45.659
Sure.

363
00:19:48.143 --> 00:19:50.193
You're okay with this?

364
00:19:50.319 --> 00:19:53.319
You know how many people
died here last night?

365
00:19:54.628 --> 00:19:56.198
Fourteen.

366
00:19:58.588 --> 00:20:00.628
Those things killed
14 of my people.

367
00:20:00.764 --> 00:20:04.774
There are pieces of them
lying all over this hill.

368
00:20:04.899 --> 00:20:08.339
And I don't think the others
are coming back any time soon.

369
00:20:11.645 --> 00:20:13.945
So. we might as well use
the house for something.

370
00:20:17.564 --> 00:20:19.224
Keep going.

371
00:20:23.178 --> 00:20:24.398
Wait right there.

372
00:20:33.493 --> 00:20:34.933
Let's go.

373
00:20:43.546 --> 00:20:45.106
You're gonna sit tight here.

374
00:20:45.244 --> 00:20:47.814
I'll be back before dark.

375
00:20:47.942 --> 00:20:52.432
I've got a few things in town
to wrap up before we head out.

376
00:20:52.555 --> 00:20:53.765
Head out where?

377
00:20:53.904 --> 00:20:56.474
Find our way home.

378
00:20:56.603 --> 00:20:59.483
You won't need those.

379
00:20:59.606 --> 00:21:02.606
I'm not going anywhere.

380
00:21:02.739 --> 00:21:05.349
I wanna help.

381
00:21:06.526 --> 00:21:09.526
All I've ever
wanted to do is help.

382
00:21:09.659 --> 00:21:11.569
There's nothing to
chain you to here anyway.

383
00:21:11.705 --> 00:21:13.445
If you run--

384
00:21:13.576 --> 00:21:15.266
I understand.

385
00:21:19.713 --> 00:21:20.983
I'll be back.

386
00:21:34.641 --> 00:21:45.001
♪

387
00:22:00.928 --> 00:22:03.058
My God.

388
00:22:06.237 --> 00:22:08.677
Boyd.

389
00:22:08.805 --> 00:22:11.025
Here. Come on.

390
00:22:19.207 --> 00:22:26.557
♪

391
00:22:26.693 --> 00:22:30.523
Welcome to your
worst nightmare.

392
00:22:30.653 --> 00:22:32.183
Look.

393
00:22:32.307 --> 00:22:36.917
it's a--
it's a lot to unpack.

394
00:22:37.051 --> 00:22:40.531
Just take it slow.

395
00:22:40.663 --> 00:22:43.493
I'll explain more
at the diner.

396
00:22:43.623 --> 00:22:45.763
At the what?

397
00:22:45.886 --> 00:22:48.146
The diner.
It's. uh...

398
00:22:48.279 --> 00:22:50.109
Meet me over there.

399
00:22:54.329 --> 00:22:57.109
Hey.
You okay?

400
00:22:59.856 --> 00:23:02.636
No. not really.

401
00:23:02.772 --> 00:23:05.042
That's what you people
do every night here?

402
00:23:05.166 --> 00:23:08.736
Here?
You hide and pray?

403
00:23:08.865 --> 00:23:12.905
Well. there's really
not much else we can do.

404
00:23:13.043 --> 00:23:16.613
And you don't know
anything else about this place?

405
00:23:16.743 --> 00:23:18.703
Who built it?
How long's it been here?

406
00:23:18.832 --> 00:23:23.402
Look. what we know
is what you see.

407
00:23:24.359 --> 00:23:26.799
And the people here.

408
00:23:26.927 --> 00:23:31.367
they just-- they're just tryin'
to live through the night.

409
00:23:31.497 --> 00:23:34.407
Doesn't give us much time
for anything else.

410
00:23:37.241 --> 00:23:38.681
You gotta start
working together.

411
00:23:38.808 --> 00:23:41.028
That's a little
easier said than done.

412
00:23:41.158 --> 00:23:42.288
Yeah. Right.

413
00:23:42.421 --> 00:23:45.251
So. you start small. right?

414
00:23:45.380 --> 00:23:47.250
Gather your resources.

415
00:23:47.382 --> 00:23:50.602
create a system. making sure
everybody's covered at night.

416
00:23:50.733 --> 00:23:52.693
Nobody hides
in the same place twice.

417
00:23:52.822 --> 00:23:54.822
You gotta get
these people to start

418
00:23:54.955 --> 00:23:57.035
looking out for each other.
taking care of each other.

419
00:23:57.174 --> 00:24:00.484
and then. you build from there.

420
00:24:03.703 --> 00:24:04.573
Okay.

421
00:24:06.183 --> 00:24:09.453
But where do we start?

422
00:24:10.884 --> 00:24:13.364
All right.

423
00:24:13.495 --> 00:24:15.885
Once we have
everything inventoried.

424
00:24:16.019 --> 00:24:18.369
we're gonna start
rationing it out.

425
00:24:18.500 --> 00:24:20.760
Donna here is
in charge of resupply.

426
00:24:20.894 --> 00:24:23.114
So. you need anything.
you go see her.

427
00:24:23.244 --> 00:24:25.384
Abby is gonna be
drawing up a system

428
00:24:25.507 --> 00:24:26.897
for where we spend
the nights.

429
00:24:27.030 --> 00:24:28.770
We're gonna start
digging up some new spots.

430
00:24:28.902 --> 00:24:30.952
make sure we are
constantly rotating.

431
00:24:31.078 --> 00:24:33.118
Let's not make it easy
for these things.

432
00:24:33.254 --> 00:24:35.744
Come on.
What do you got?

433
00:24:35.865 --> 00:24:37.605
All right.

434
00:24:51.098 --> 00:24:52.968
Hey.

435
00:24:54.971 --> 00:24:56.631
What are you doing?

436
00:25:00.020 --> 00:25:01.590
Are you hungry?

437
00:25:03.414 --> 00:25:05.634
No. Not really.

438
00:25:13.468 --> 00:25:15.638
Have you eaten anything?

439
00:25:17.994 --> 00:25:21.004
I don't know. No.

440
00:25:22.521 --> 00:25:26.481
I'm gonna make you some food.

441
00:25:26.612 --> 00:25:28.702
Are you and Dad still
getting a divorce?

442
00:25:30.790 --> 00:25:32.880
I. uh...

443
00:25:33.009 --> 00:25:36.189
I really don't have an answer
for you right now.

444
00:25:36.317 --> 00:25:38.227
It's a simple question.

445
00:25:41.278 --> 00:25:43.238
It's not
that simple. honey.

446
00:25:48.982 --> 00:25:51.032
Hey. Hey.

447
00:25:53.073 --> 00:25:55.253
You said you loved each other.

448
00:25:57.947 --> 00:25:59.727
We do.

449
00:26:01.211 --> 00:26:03.651
Then why?

450
00:26:03.779 --> 00:26:05.129
-Is it me?
-No.

451
00:26:05.259 --> 00:26:06.739
Did I do something wrong?

452
00:26:06.869 --> 00:26:08.919
Oh. God. no.
No. no. no. No.

453
00:26:09.045 --> 00:26:11.785
No. honey. you didn't
do anything wrong. Don't...

454
00:26:11.918 --> 00:26:13.348
No.

455
00:26:17.880 --> 00:26:19.270
Listen.

456
00:26:21.101 --> 00:26:24.801
There are things that
you'll only understand

457
00:26:24.931 --> 00:26:27.411
when you become a parent.

458
00:26:27.542 --> 00:26:31.022
One of those things...

459
00:26:31.154 --> 00:26:33.294
is that you live
for your children.

460
00:26:37.030 --> 00:26:41.690
Your only job is-- is
to love them and protect them.

461
00:26:47.083 --> 00:26:49.703
So when Thomas died...

462
00:26:51.958 --> 00:26:53.788
something inside of me broke.

463
00:26:59.008 --> 00:27:01.098
And I have
no idea how to fix it.

464
00:27:07.974 --> 00:27:10.114
I keep reliving that day.

465
00:27:13.022 --> 00:27:14.762
It was just
such a normal day.

466
00:27:16.722 --> 00:27:19.812
You and Ethan were
in the next room.

467
00:27:19.942 --> 00:27:21.382
Your Dad and I
were in the kitchen.

468
00:27:21.509 --> 00:27:24.639
and Thomas was in his changing
table right between us.

469
00:27:37.133 --> 00:27:38.793
Then the phone rang.

470
00:27:41.137 --> 00:27:42.657
I reached for the diaper

471
00:27:42.791 --> 00:27:44.841
and your father reached
for the phone and...

472
00:27:47.187 --> 00:27:52.017
we just turned for one second...

473
00:27:52.148 --> 00:27:54.538
just one fucking second...

474
00:27:54.673 --> 00:27:57.683
and he rolled off the table.

475
00:28:06.032 --> 00:28:09.172
Your father
is the love of my life.

476
00:28:13.213 --> 00:28:15.433
But sometimes I see him and...

477
00:28:18.435 --> 00:28:22.045
I hear
that fucking phone ring.

478
00:28:22.178 --> 00:28:25.828
Why didn't you tell me that?

479
00:28:29.490 --> 00:28:32.970
Because no matter
how grown up you are.

480
00:28:33.102 --> 00:28:35.712
you're always
gonna be my little girl.

481
00:28:39.674 --> 00:28:41.764
So we pretended...

482
00:28:45.071 --> 00:28:46.861
yeah. that everything was fine.

483
00:28:49.510 --> 00:28:51.730
I think that just made
everything worse.

484
00:28:55.995 --> 00:28:57.735
I'm sorry.

485
00:28:59.215 --> 00:29:02.035
I'm sorry. too.

486
00:29:10.357 --> 00:29:11.967
Let us in!

487
00:29:15.231 --> 00:29:19.061
There's gonna be trouble if you
don't move outta the way!

488
00:29:19.192 --> 00:29:20.632
-Let us in!
-Hey. hey. hey. hey!

489
00:29:20.759 --> 00:29:22.109
What the hell's going on?!

490
00:29:23.805 --> 00:29:24.935
Tom. Eli.
what the hell are you doing?

491
00:29:25.067 --> 00:29:27.157
We got people from Colony House
in our houses.

492
00:29:27.287 --> 00:29:28.897
using our supplies!

493
00:29:29.028 --> 00:29:30.378
If I gotta choose between me

494
00:29:30.507 --> 00:29:32.337
and some asshole from
Colony House raiding this place.

495
00:29:32.466 --> 00:29:35.026
-then it's gonna be me!
-Nobody's raiding anything!

496
00:29:35.164 --> 00:29:36.644
Well. those things weren't
supposed to be able

497
00:29:36.775 --> 00:29:39.425
to get into Colony House either.
and look how that turned out!

498
00:29:39.560 --> 00:29:41.080
-Exactly.
-Alright. So then. you guys--

499
00:29:41.214 --> 00:29:43.044
you just wanna
throw it all away?

500
00:29:43.172 --> 00:29:45.042
Start acting like animals
and make it all worse?

501
00:29:45.174 --> 00:29:47.134
Look. we're gonna
figure this out.

502
00:29:47.263 --> 00:29:50.613
Just-- just go home.

503
00:29:50.745 --> 00:29:53.485
Just go home. please.

504
00:30:02.278 --> 00:30:04.928
They... scared.

505
00:30:05.064 --> 00:30:06.504
Yeah.

506
00:30:17.728 --> 00:30:20.428
Those things come out at night.

507
00:30:20.557 --> 00:30:24.557
They walking around in
the forest during the daytime?

508
00:30:24.692 --> 00:30:27.612
Not as far as we can tell.

509
00:30:27.738 --> 00:30:30.388
There might be
resources out there.

510
00:30:30.524 --> 00:30:32.744
We go scavenging
during the daytime.

511
00:30:32.874 --> 00:30:35.624
never know what
we might find.

512
00:30:35.746 --> 00:30:38.576
Yeah.
Good luck findin' volunteers.

513
00:30:38.706 --> 00:30:42.706
Right.
We'll work on that part.

514
00:30:42.841 --> 00:30:44.491
How long were you
in the military?

515
00:30:45.800 --> 00:30:47.980
Uh. almost 30 years.

516
00:30:48.107 --> 00:30:49.847
Hm.

517
00:30:49.978 --> 00:30:51.678
Set up operations
in some of the biggest.

518
00:30:51.806 --> 00:30:54.676
baddest clusterfucks
on the planet.

519
00:30:54.809 --> 00:30:57.329
And your wife?

520
00:30:57.464 --> 00:30:59.604
Abby was a Marine.

521
00:30:59.727 --> 00:31:02.557
She's the badass
in the family.

522
00:31:02.686 --> 00:31:03.856
Yeah.

523
00:31:16.178 --> 00:31:19.228
Mom. you okay?

524
00:31:19.355 --> 00:31:21.575
Yeah.

525
00:31:21.705 --> 00:31:23.835
Yeah. I'm fine. I...

526
00:31:23.969 --> 00:31:27.099
I was just thinking
about this dream I had

527
00:31:27.233 --> 00:31:28.933
when I was a little girl.

528
00:31:29.061 --> 00:31:30.891
I was...

529
00:31:34.022 --> 00:31:36.332
Never mind.
We should go help your dad.

530
00:31:36.459 --> 00:31:38.199
Lots to do.

531
00:31:45.207 --> 00:31:47.077
Can't go. not now.

532
00:31:47.209 --> 00:31:49.169
Damn near had
a riot at the diner.

533
00:31:49.298 --> 00:31:51.208
But this is exactly
why you said you had to go.

534
00:31:51.344 --> 00:31:53.744
Things are coming apart.
It's already starting to happen.

535
00:31:53.868 --> 00:31:55.738
We lost over a dozen people
last night.

536
00:31:55.870 --> 00:31:58.700
And we'll lose more if...
if they start to panic.

537
00:31:58.829 --> 00:32:00.479
-At least if you--
-Kenny. enough.

538
00:32:00.614 --> 00:32:02.404
I'll stay until
things settle down.

539
00:32:02.529 --> 00:32:04.619
And what if they don't?

540
00:32:04.748 --> 00:32:06.578
What if they don't?

541
00:32:06.707 --> 00:32:07.747
Am I interrupting?

542
00:32:07.882 --> 00:32:09.012
No. come on in.

543
00:32:09.144 --> 00:32:10.104
Sheriff. please--

544
00:32:10.232 --> 00:32:13.582
Kenny. we're done. Okay?

545
00:32:13.714 --> 00:32:16.504
We're not done.

546
00:32:18.762 --> 00:32:20.942
I said. we're not done.

547
00:32:22.288 --> 00:32:24.118
You told me you had to go.

548
00:32:24.246 --> 00:32:26.116
You told me
that I had to step up

549
00:32:26.248 --> 00:32:28.898
and be strong
while you were gone.

550
00:32:29.034 --> 00:32:30.734
You told me we were
running out of time.

551
00:32:30.861 --> 00:32:33.301
and what part
of that's changed? Huh?

552
00:32:33.429 --> 00:32:35.739
We've all been sitting
around the last few months.

553
00:32:35.866 --> 00:32:37.476
acting like those
talismans were a solution.

554
00:32:37.607 --> 00:32:40.347
Like they made us safe?

555
00:32:40.480 --> 00:32:43.740
Well. guess what.
We were never safe.

556
00:32:43.874 --> 00:32:46.184
Those talismans were a Band-Aid.

557
00:32:46.312 --> 00:32:48.752
a-- a temporary reprieve.

558
00:32:49.924 --> 00:32:51.974
Things were never okay here.

559
00:32:52.100 --> 00:32:55.970
and things are never
going to be okay here.

560
00:32:58.802 --> 00:33:03.892
We need to find a way home

561
00:33:04.025 --> 00:33:06.805
or else every
single person here

562
00:33:06.941 --> 00:33:08.771
is gonna end up
exactly like Father Khatri.

563
00:33:11.859 --> 00:33:14.509
There are answers out there.

564
00:33:14.644 --> 00:33:17.474
and you're going to find them.

565
00:33:17.604 --> 00:33:19.214
And in the meantime.

566
00:33:19.345 --> 00:33:21.865
you need to get over
what happened last night.

567
00:33:22.000 --> 00:33:23.220
You need to get
your shit together

568
00:33:23.349 --> 00:33:25.309
and be the scary hard-ass
that you've always been

569
00:33:25.438 --> 00:33:28.348
because that's who people
need you to be right now.

570
00:33:28.484 --> 00:33:32.054
And if we're not gonna fight
like hell to go home.

571
00:33:32.184 --> 00:33:34.664
then we might as well swallow
a fucking bullet right now.

572
00:33:36.362 --> 00:33:38.632
Is that what you want?

573
00:33:52.117 --> 00:33:54.767
I didn't know the little
bastard had that in him.

574
00:33:56.860 --> 00:33:58.600
Now. how about you explain

575
00:33:58.732 --> 00:34:00.862
what the fuck
he was talking about?

576
00:34:00.995 --> 00:34:02.865
Where exactly are you going?

577
00:34:02.997 --> 00:34:06.347
Let's take a walk.
I'll explain on the way.

578
00:34:08.089 --> 00:34:09.259
Come on. man!
Whoa. whoa. whoa!

579
00:34:10.918 --> 00:34:12.828
Come on!
Help me out a little bit here.

580
00:34:12.963 --> 00:34:14.053
Hey!

581
00:34:15.357 --> 00:34:16.917
Look what I found!

582
00:34:17.055 --> 00:34:19.405
Okay. what? Where--
where did you--?

583
00:34:19.535 --> 00:34:22.405
I-- He was about half
a mile out. eating some grass.

584
00:34:22.538 --> 00:34:23.968
There are chickens
out there too.

585
00:34:24.105 --> 00:34:25.795
Tomorrow.
I'm gonna set up some traps.

586
00:34:25.933 --> 00:34:26.853
There's chickens in the forest?

587
00:34:26.977 --> 00:34:28.017
Yep.

588
00:34:28.153 --> 00:34:30.113
Hey. you know what?
Grab some people.

589
00:34:30.242 --> 00:34:32.512
We need to start rebuilding
that. uh. pen outside the barn.

590
00:34:32.635 --> 00:34:33.845
Okay? Hey! Hey!

591
00:34:33.984 --> 00:34:34.904
Hey.

592
00:34:35.029 --> 00:34:36.549
-I found a goat.
-He got a goat.

593
00:34:36.683 --> 00:34:38.033
Yeah. that's great.

594
00:34:38.163 --> 00:34:40.383
Hey. uh. look.
I need to talk to you.

595
00:34:40.513 --> 00:34:42.213
All right. Hey. could you
take him off my hands?

596
00:34:42.341 --> 00:34:43.821
No.

597
00:34:43.951 --> 00:34:45.041
Yeah. no. you got it.
Yeah. yeah.

598
00:34:45.170 --> 00:34:46.610
He's not exactly what
I'd call cooperative.

599
00:34:46.736 --> 00:34:47.606
but just hold the rope.

600
00:34:47.737 --> 00:34:48.607
-Yeah.
-You got it.

601
00:34:48.738 --> 00:34:50.178
-I. uh...
-You believe that?

602
00:34:50.305 --> 00:34:52.475
I knew I was gonna find
something out in those woods.

603
00:34:52.612 --> 00:34:54.832
I ain't think it was gonna be
livestock. but I'll take it.

604
00:34:54.962 --> 00:34:55.922
Who knows what else might be--

605
00:34:56.050 --> 00:34:57.490
You need to stop
going out there.

606
00:34:57.617 --> 00:34:59.007
What?

607
00:34:59.140 --> 00:35:01.450
It's Mom.
She's not doing well. Okay?

608
00:35:01.577 --> 00:35:03.407
I mean. you've been going out
there for weeks now.

609
00:35:03.536 --> 00:35:05.446
and you're not seeing
what's happening here.

610
00:35:05.581 --> 00:35:07.891
I think this place is. like.
starting to get to her.

611
00:35:08.018 --> 00:35:10.328
Okay.

612
00:35:10.456 --> 00:35:13.496
Look. I know you're scared. man.

613
00:35:13.633 --> 00:35:18.333
I'm fricking terrified.
But do me a favor. Look around.

614
00:35:18.464 --> 00:35:21.474
The things we are doing
are working.

615
00:35:21.597 --> 00:35:24.027
There are things out
in those woods that can help us.

616
00:35:24.165 --> 00:35:27.815
things that might even--
All I know. all I know is that

617
00:35:27.951 --> 00:35:31.691
the second we stop looking for
answers. that's when we lose.

618
00:35:31.825 --> 00:35:33.475
Okay. so. then why don't
we just get someone else

619
00:35:33.609 --> 00:35:35.789
to go and look for a while?
Dad. we need you here.

620
00:35:35.916 --> 00:35:37.866
Mom needs you here!

621
00:35:38.005 --> 00:35:42.005
Okay. look. she-- she's not...

622
00:35:42.140 --> 00:35:44.140
You know. sometimes.
I-I see her just standing.

623
00:35:44.272 --> 00:35:46.972
staring off in the middle
of the road. like she's--

624
00:35:47.101 --> 00:35:50.371
Your mom... Your mom is
as tough as they come.

625
00:35:50.496 --> 00:35:52.626
Iron Abby. remember?

626
00:35:52.759 --> 00:35:56.589
Now. I know this is hard.
but this is what we have to do.

627
00:35:56.719 --> 00:35:58.069
at least for now.

628
00:35:58.199 --> 00:36:01.159
You're not even listening
to what I'm saying to you!

629
00:36:01.289 --> 00:36:04.029
Look. look. okay. okay.
Look. look. Look. look.

630
00:36:04.162 --> 00:36:07.032
We got about four hours
of daylight left. right?

631
00:36:07.165 --> 00:36:09.945
Help your mom get everybody
secured. tucked away.

632
00:36:10.080 --> 00:36:12.430
And when I get home
tonight. we will talk.

633
00:36:12.561 --> 00:36:14.221
I promise.

634
00:36:15.912 --> 00:36:17.912
Dad. please...

635
00:36:18.045 --> 00:36:20.345
just stay.

636
00:36:20.482 --> 00:36:23.312
We will talk tonight.

637
00:36:23.442 --> 00:36:24.752
Okay?

638
00:36:26.793 --> 00:36:28.753
Go help your mom.

639
00:36:52.601 --> 00:36:54.391
What are you doin' out here?

640
00:36:57.650 --> 00:37:00.780
Well. you belong to someone.

641
00:37:02.481 --> 00:37:03.921
Someone out here maybe?

642
00:37:08.313 --> 00:37:10.923
You live out here
with someone. buddy?

643
00:37:11.054 --> 00:37:12.624
-It's okay.

644
00:37:12.752 --> 00:37:15.022
It's okay.

645
00:37:16.538 --> 00:37:18.798
It's okay.
I'm not gonna hurt you.

646
00:37:18.932 --> 00:37:20.932
I just wanna get
a closer look.

647
00:37:25.547 --> 00:37:26.897
Hey! Hey! Hey!

648
00:37:34.164 --> 00:37:35.914
Hey!

649
00:37:39.300 --> 00:37:42.350
What the...

650
00:37:42.477 --> 00:37:45.997
♪

651
00:37:46.133 --> 00:37:49.053
No.

652
00:37:49.179 --> 00:37:50.959
No. no.

653
00:37:51.094 --> 00:38:01.024
♪

654
00:38:05.283 --> 00:38:08.593
Fuck!

655
00:38:29.655 --> 00:38:31.305
What?

656
00:38:55.028 --> 00:38:56.328
What the...

657
00:39:46.819 --> 00:39:57.049
♪

658
00:40:22.724 --> 00:40:24.814
Luck. not skill.

659
00:40:27.990 --> 00:40:30.650
Sheriff Stevens.

660
00:40:30.776 --> 00:40:33.466
Heard you had a rough go of it
last night.

661
00:40:36.085 --> 00:40:39.085
Sorry about Father Khatri.

662
00:40:39.219 --> 00:40:41.219
Oh. I appreciate that.

663
00:40:41.351 --> 00:40:42.791
I. uh...

664
00:40:44.877 --> 00:40:48.657
Not sure if you heard.
but I'm setting off today.

665
00:40:48.794 --> 00:40:50.754
Gonna find us a way
outta this place.

666
00:40:50.883 --> 00:40:53.363
So. in other words. you're about
to go off into the woods

667
00:40:53.494 --> 00:40:56.064
with no idea
what you're looking for.

668
00:40:56.192 --> 00:40:58.542
Because that worked
so well last time.

669
00:40:58.673 --> 00:40:59.593
Hey.

670
00:40:59.718 --> 00:41:01.238
Right?

671
00:41:01.371 --> 00:41:03.641
Fatima. would you
give us a second?

672
00:41:03.765 --> 00:41:05.585
Yeah. of course.

673
00:41:05.724 --> 00:41:07.034
Thank you.

674
00:41:15.081 --> 00:41:17.741
You wanna be angry with me.

675
00:41:17.866 --> 00:41:20.346
you wanna hate me. that's fine.

676
00:41:21.130 --> 00:41:24.350
But I'm gonna say
a couple things and. uh.

677
00:41:24.482 --> 00:41:28.532
and you're gonna listen.
whether you want to or not.

678
00:41:30.662 --> 00:41:32.792
Go ahead.

679
00:41:32.925 --> 00:41:34.315
If something happens
to me out there.

680
00:41:34.448 --> 00:41:38.448
if I don't... make it back.

681
00:41:38.583 --> 00:41:42.153
I never want you to regret
what you didn't say.

682
00:41:44.371 --> 00:41:47.071
I never want you to feel...

683
00:41:49.463 --> 00:41:52.813
I won't be here to
tell you that it's okay.

684
00:41:54.860 --> 00:41:58.690
So. I'm telling you now.

685
00:41:58.820 --> 00:42:02.690
Man. it's okay.

686
00:42:02.824 --> 00:42:06.874
And that you are my son.

687
00:42:07.002 --> 00:42:08.532
Mine.

688
00:42:10.092 --> 00:42:12.832
I love you.

689
00:42:12.965 --> 00:42:16.525
and I am proud of the man
that you have become.

690
00:42:18.579 --> 00:42:22.319
And not a single day goes by
when that hasn't been true.

691
00:42:25.455 --> 00:42:27.105
Okay?

692
00:42:31.026 --> 00:42:32.986
Yeah.

693
00:42:33.115 --> 00:42:35.675
Yeah. it's okay.

694
00:42:35.814 --> 00:42:37.564
Okay.

695
00:42:43.473 --> 00:42:45.133
Okay.

696
00:42:55.877 --> 00:42:58.307
How'd that go?

697
00:42:58.445 --> 00:43:00.745
About as well
as could be expected.

698
00:43:00.882 --> 00:43:03.282
He'll come 'round.

699
00:43:05.191 --> 00:43:06.581
You really going?

700
00:43:08.847 --> 00:43:10.277
Looks like.

701
00:43:12.764 --> 00:43:16.294
You and me. we've had our
differences. but I just. uh...

702
00:43:18.160 --> 00:43:20.380
Thank you...

703
00:43:20.510 --> 00:43:23.340
for looking after him.

704
00:43:23.470 --> 00:43:24.780
You've done
something I couldn't.

705
00:43:24.906 --> 00:43:26.816
You did enough. Boyd.

706
00:43:26.952 --> 00:43:31.092
You did more than anyone
should ever have to.

707
00:43:31.217 --> 00:43:33.567
So. you come back. okay?

708
00:43:33.698 --> 00:43:36.178
Who the hell else
am I gonna argue with?

709
00:43:37.440 --> 00:43:39.140
Sure you'll find someone.

710
00:43:39.268 --> 00:43:40.308
-Fuck off.

711
00:43:40.443 --> 00:43:42.183
-What?
-Come on.

712
00:43:44.012 --> 00:43:45.842
Now. get the fuck outta here

713
00:43:45.971 --> 00:43:49.021
before people start
thinking we're friends.

714
00:43:49.148 --> 00:43:50.278
Yes. ma'am.

715
00:44:00.159 --> 00:44:02.899
I'm gonna say something to you
that might make you hate me.

716
00:44:03.031 --> 00:44:05.291
and if it does. that's okay.

717
00:44:07.732 --> 00:44:10.912
What happened
wasn't your Dad's fault.

718
00:44:11.039 --> 00:44:14.089
and it wasn't yours.
It was this place.

719
00:44:14.216 --> 00:44:18.566
I wasn't here. I may not have
seen it. but I know your Dad.

720
00:44:18.699 --> 00:44:21.009
I know that if
there was anything.

721
00:44:21.136 --> 00:44:23.696
anything else he could've done.
he would've done it.

722
00:44:26.011 --> 00:44:29.671
What happened was so awful...

723
00:44:29.797 --> 00:44:33.887
it's almost inconceivable.
and it fills you with rage.

724
00:44:34.019 --> 00:44:35.669
rage that you needed
to put somewhere.

725
00:44:35.803 --> 00:44:38.413
And this whole time.
your dad let you put it on him

726
00:44:38.545 --> 00:44:41.675
because that's what parents do.

727
00:44:41.809 --> 00:44:44.549
But did you. for a second.
stop to consider

728
00:44:44.682 --> 00:44:47.552
what that day was like for him.

729
00:44:47.685 --> 00:44:52.245
what he's carried every
second of every day since?

730
00:44:59.131 --> 00:45:01.701
If you don't get up
and go after him right now.

731
00:45:01.829 --> 00:45:05.139
you're gonna regret it
for the rest of your life.

732
00:45:38.648 --> 00:45:39.818
What's--

733
00:45:41.216 --> 00:45:42.516
Babe?

734
00:45:45.003 --> 00:45:46.533
Ab?

735
00:45:50.008 --> 00:45:51.788
What's happening. Abs?

736
00:45:53.054 --> 00:45:54.404
What's going on. Abs?

737
00:45:58.668 --> 00:46:00.888
Abs?

738
00:46:01.019 --> 00:46:02.459
Abby?

739
00:46:02.585 --> 00:46:04.325
Oh. God. Oh. God.

740
00:46:05.675 --> 00:46:07.715
Ab--

741
00:46:07.852 --> 00:46:10.902
Please.
Please. why are you doing this?

742
00:46:11.029 --> 00:46:12.549
It's okay.

743
00:46:12.682 --> 00:46:16.082
It's not real.
It's a nightmare.

744
00:46:16.208 --> 00:46:19.558
The only way for us to go home
is to wake everyone up.

745
00:46:19.689 --> 00:46:22.999
It's okay.
You can't die in dreams.

746
00:46:23.128 --> 00:46:24.478
Everything's gonna be okay.

747
00:46:24.607 --> 00:46:26.907
Abby.
Abby. stop! Stop!

748
00:46:27.045 --> 00:46:28.515
S-s-stop.

749
00:46:28.655 --> 00:46:31.525
No. No.

750
00:46:31.658 --> 00:46:34.528
Hey. Hey.
I found something.

751
00:46:34.661 --> 00:46:35.791
s-something I think
is gonna help us.

752
00:46:35.923 --> 00:46:38.103
You didn't come back
before it got dark.

753
00:46:38.230 --> 00:46:39.360
There's no way you could
have survived out there.

754
00:46:39.492 --> 00:46:42.062
not if it was real.

755
00:46:42.190 --> 00:46:43.760
Yeah.

756
00:46:43.888 --> 00:46:47.588
It's time to wake up.
It's time to wake everybody up.

757
00:46:47.717 --> 00:46:50.547
Baby. please.

758
00:46:50.677 --> 00:46:52.157
Baby...

759
00:46:54.246 --> 00:46:55.636
♪ If I had a boat

760
00:46:55.769 --> 00:46:57.379
♪ I'd go out on the ocean

761
00:46:57.510 --> 00:46:59.290
Right! If I had a pony?

762
00:46:59.425 --> 00:47:01.075
-Mom! Mom!
♪ If I had a pony

763
00:47:01.209 --> 00:47:02.169
-Mom!
-♪ I'd ride him--

764
00:47:02.297 --> 00:47:04.127
No. no!

765
00:47:57.352 --> 00:48:00.182
Dad?

766
00:48:01.356 --> 00:48:05.136
Ellis. what are
you doing out here?

767
00:48:05.273 --> 00:48:07.493
Um...

768
00:48:07.623 --> 00:48:10.323
I've been following you
since you left town.

769
00:48:10.452 --> 00:48:13.412
I've been. um...

770
00:48:13.542 --> 00:48:15.412
I've been trying to find the
courage to say something to you.

771
00:48:19.374 --> 00:48:21.814
Look. last night. when. uh.

772
00:48:21.942 --> 00:48:23.512
those things got inside
of Colony House.

773
00:48:23.639 --> 00:48:27.469
Fatima and I.
we would've died.

774
00:48:28.340 --> 00:48:31.080
I mean. there was no way
that we could've survived that.

775
00:48:33.736 --> 00:48:38.126
But the one thing that saved us.

776
00:48:38.263 --> 00:48:40.313
that saved her...

777
00:48:42.310 --> 00:48:44.270
was the talisman on the door.

778
00:48:51.406 --> 00:48:55.186
I've just been so angry
for a really long time...

779
00:48:57.847 --> 00:49:00.237
...and I. uh...

780
00:49:03.592 --> 00:49:05.162
I didn't know how to...

781
00:49:08.554 --> 00:49:11.604
But. you know. if you
didn't do what you did.

782
00:49:11.731 --> 00:49:15.041
if you didn't bring
those talismans back...

783
00:49:22.350 --> 00:49:24.050
It wasn't your fault. Dad.

784
00:49:26.659 --> 00:49:30.179
What Mom did.
it wasn't...

785
00:49:30.315 --> 00:49:32.265
It wasn't your fault.

786
00:49:35.755 --> 00:49:39.235
Look. I'm sorry.
Yeah. I'm so sorry. Dad.

787
00:49:39.367 --> 00:49:40.277
I'm so sorry.

788
00:49:40.412 --> 00:49:43.242
No. no. no. hey.
Hey. no.

789
00:49:44.503 --> 00:49:47.253
It's okay. It's all right.

790
00:49:47.375 --> 00:49:49.195
I just-- I just didn't
want you to leave

791
00:49:49.334 --> 00:49:50.554
without saying goodbye.

792
00:49:50.683 --> 00:49:52.343
This is not goodbye.

793
00:49:52.467 --> 00:49:55.207
Okay? You hear me? Huh?

794
00:49:55.340 --> 00:49:57.430
This is not goodbye.

795
00:49:57.559 --> 00:49:58.429
Okay.

796
00:49:58.560 --> 00:50:00.130
All right.

797
00:50:05.393 --> 00:50:06.393
Hey.

798
00:50:08.614 --> 00:50:09.924
What is she doing here?

799
00:50:10.050 --> 00:50:12.570
Look. I need
to take her with me. Okay?

800
00:50:12.705 --> 00:50:14.485
Wait. no. you know
what she tried to do!

801
00:50:14.620 --> 00:50:16.540
No. no. no! Hey. look. look.
I need to take her with me

802
00:50:16.665 --> 00:50:19.575
'cause she might be helpful
for us to find out

803
00:50:19.712 --> 00:50:21.502
what we're looking
for out there. okay?

804
00:50:21.627 --> 00:50:23.587
I will explain everything
to you when I get back.

805
00:50:23.716 --> 00:50:25.326
We'll have a long conversation.

806
00:50:25.457 --> 00:50:27.497
hopefully on our way
outta this place.

807
00:50:27.633 --> 00:50:31.553
But for now. right now. I just
need you to trust me. okay?

808
00:50:31.680 --> 00:50:33.860
Okay. no one can
know she's with me.

809
00:50:33.987 --> 00:50:35.417
Can you do that for me?

810
00:50:35.554 --> 00:50:38.344
Can you trust me?

811
00:50:42.648 --> 00:50:44.388
Just come back.

812
00:50:44.519 --> 00:50:46.779
Yes. sir.

813
00:50:46.913 --> 00:50:49.353
All right.

814
00:50:49.481 --> 00:50:51.791
Go on. Go.

815
00:50:51.918 --> 00:50:53.218
I love you.

816
00:50:55.530 --> 00:50:56.840
I love you. too.

817
00:50:56.966 --> 00:50:59.186
Okay.

818
00:51:02.450 --> 00:51:04.150
Yeah.

819
00:51:12.504 --> 00:51:14.944
Look. we're in a tight spot.

820
00:51:15.072 --> 00:51:17.422
No one's gonna
pretend otherwise.

821
00:51:18.118 --> 00:51:20.638
But Sheriff Boyd
is risking everything for us

822
00:51:20.773 --> 00:51:22.603
out there in the forest.

823
00:51:22.731 --> 00:51:24.991
The least we can do is...

824
00:51:25.125 --> 00:51:27.645
keep ourselves
together while he does.

825
00:51:27.780 --> 00:51:30.260
So that means that we're gonna
do things a little differently

826
00:51:30.391 --> 00:51:31.571
going forwards.

827
00:51:31.697 --> 00:51:34.867
No more Colony House.
no more town.

828
00:51:35.004 --> 00:51:37.664
We're a community. so...

829
00:51:37.790 --> 00:51:40.710
we do this together.

830
00:51:40.836 --> 00:51:43.396
All you Colony House folk.

831
00:51:43.535 --> 00:51:45.745
I don't want any of you
being shitty houseguests.

832
00:51:45.885 --> 00:51:48.885
Now. we're gonna get
the house put back together.

833
00:51:49.018 --> 00:51:50.848
but first of all.

834
00:51:50.977 --> 00:51:53.547
Jim here has an idea about
a way we might be able to get

835
00:51:53.675 --> 00:51:55.585
a signal to folks
back in the world.

836
00:51:55.721 --> 00:51:58.681
So we can either
put our energy towards

837
00:51:58.811 --> 00:52:00.731
boarding up a bunch
of broken windows.

838
00:52:00.856 --> 00:52:03.636
or we can help build
something that gets us all

839
00:52:03.772 --> 00:52:06.342
out of this shithole.

840
00:52:06.471 --> 00:52:07.341
Jim?

841
00:52:11.606 --> 00:52:14.646
Well. we're gonna need supplies.

842
00:52:14.783 --> 00:52:17.573
anything we can get
our hands on.

843
00:52:17.699 --> 00:52:20.439
We're gonna need batteries.
anything with a charge.

844
00:52:20.572 --> 00:52:23.712
But most of all.
we're gonna need people.

845
00:52:23.836 --> 00:52:26.526
The sooner we get this built.

846
00:52:26.665 --> 00:52:28.535
the sooner we can all go home.

847
00:52:35.674 --> 00:52:38.424
Hey. You find him?

848
00:52:38.546 --> 00:52:39.626
♪ And if I had a pony

849
00:52:39.765 --> 00:52:41.765
-Yeah.
-♪ I'd ride him on my boat

850
00:52:41.897 --> 00:52:43.637
-You okay?
-♪ And we could all together

851
00:52:43.769 --> 00:52:47.599
-No.
-♪ Go out on the ocean

852
00:52:52.995 --> 00:52:55.425
♪ And if I were Roy Rogers

853
00:52:55.563 --> 00:52:57.873
♪ I'd sure enough be single

854
00:53:04.616 --> 00:53:05.826
Can't take any chances.

855
00:53:07.880 --> 00:53:09.620
♪ Then we'd buy a boat

856
00:53:09.751 --> 00:53:12.361
♪ And on the sea. we'd sail

857
00:53:14.147 --> 00:53:16.447
♪ And if I had a boat

858
00:53:16.584 --> 00:53:18.674
♪ I'd go out on the ocean

859
00:53:20.762 --> 00:53:22.852
Let's go.

860
00:53:40.608 --> 00:53:42.568
♪
